Articles.Content:
I just checked to see if there is an updated version of MechJeb and noticed that the most current version is 2.5.8.0. But somehow I have version 2.5.9.0. I can't remember where I found it. I do remember I had a bit of trouble getting it to work, but I ended up just replacing the dll. It seems to function fine for what I use it for which is not much, just docking and landing.

Does anyone have any idea what I have here?

I fixed the title. I accidentally hit a 9 instead of 0 in the title. The zip file is named MechJeb2-2.5.9.0-643.zip.

Edited November 13, 2016 by Ty Tan Tu

Latest dev build (1.2) build is currently #648

https://ksp.sarbian.com/jenkins/job/MechJeb2-Dev/
Thanks Curveball Anders. I thought I was going crazy. It looks like there have been some tweaks to docking since the version I have. I think I will try the new 648 build.
